@node "Intro" "Introduction"

Did you ever want to have lotsa different default icons??? But you don`t
wanna spend lotsa of your memory for this??? Then this might be the way
to get a right solution.

The way is easy ... instead of copying the ENV directory into the RAM you
simply have got a second ENV directory on your HD.
So read on and @{"Install it!" link "Insta" 0}

But don`t forget to read the @{"Disclaimer" link "Discl" 0}!!

By the way ... I know, there are many other solutions for this problem
on AmiNet and so on, but no one of those I tried were running for 100%.
If you try this one you won`t miss it then ... (((-8 ...

This one has been released on January, 6th in the year 1997!!! (So a happy
New Year to all of you! 8-) AMIGA rulez ... INTEL OUTSIDE ... (8

@endnode

